The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | TCS picks Ramadorai successor
                                                                                                               TCS picks Ramadorai successor
          OUR BUREAU                              
	Mumbai, May 26: N. Chandrasekaran will take over as the new chief executive officer of Tata Consultancy Services Indias largest software company  on October 6.        
	Chandrasekaran, who will replace S. Ramadorai, is now the chief operating officer and executive director of TCS.        
	Ramadorai has headed TCS since August 2004. His five-year tenure was due to end on August 8.        
	The board of directors of TCS today gave Ramadorai a two-month extension till October 5. Ramadorai turns 65 in October, which is the mandatory retirement age from executive positions within the Tata group.        
	In a notice sent to the Bombay Stock Exchange, TCS said Chandrasekaran would be the CEO-designate.         
	Chandrasekaran joined TCS in 1987 and moved up to the position of COO in September 2007. Prior to becoming the COO, he was executive vice-president and head of global operations.                                                                                                                                        
